<div class="section" id="ideas">
  <div class="sec-label">
    <div class="sec-label-text">Problem<br>Space</div>
    <div class="sec-label-num">03</div>
  </div>
  <div class="sec-body">
    <p class="rfb-intro">RFBs — "Requests for Builders" — are our version of <a href="https://www.ycombinator.com/rfs" target="_blank">YC's Requests for Startups</a>. Five open problems in the agent economy that we think are worth solving. Click any to explore. <strong>The best submissions always start from a specific frustration.</strong></p>
    <div class="rfb-list">

      <div class="rfb-item" id="rfb-1">
        <button class="rfb-trigger" onclick="toggleRFB('rfb-1')">
          <div class="rfb-n">RFB 01</div>
          <div class="rfb-trigger-main">
            <div class="rfb-t-title">Agent Discovery &amp; Reputation Networks</div>
            <div class="rfb-t-sub">Your agent offers a service. How do other agents find it and decide to trust it?</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rfb-toggle">+</div>
        </button>
        <div class="rfb-body">
          <div class="rfb-body-inner">
            <div class="rfb-problem">Your AI agent offers a service — trading signals, design work, analysis. How do other agents find you and decide to trust you?</div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">What builders create</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Agent marketplaces with reputation and ranking algorithms</li>
              <li>Agent recommendation systems, collaborative filtering for AI</li>
              <li>Quality scoring mechanisms where other agents rate your agent</li>
              <li>Agent advertising platforms: how do agents market to agents?</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Questions worth exploring</div>
            <ul class="ql">
              <li>Do agents form cliques and networks like humans?</li>
              <li>Can agent reputation be gamed? How do you prevent Sybil attacks?</li>
              <li>Do specialized agent networks emerge — trading agents only talk to trading agents?</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="rfb-ex"><div class="rfb-ex-lbl">Example</div><p>"AgentGraph" — Yelp for AI agents. Agents build profiles, other agents review them, and on-chain payment history serves as the reputation signal.</p></div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Traction metrics</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Number of agents and agent startups using your product for discovery and reputation</li>
              <li>Agent-to-agent transactions · Network density · Reputation score distribution</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rfb-item" id="rfb-2">
        <button class="rfb-trigger" onclick="toggleRFB('rfb-2')">
          <div class="rfb-n">RFB 02</div>
          <div class="rfb-trigger-main">
            <div class="rfb-t-title">Real-Time Agent Coordination</div>
            <div class="rfb-t-sub">Multiple agents need to coordinate in real-time. Voice calls. Live auctions. Streaming services.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rfb-toggle">+</div>
        </button>
        <div class="rfb-body">
          <div class="rfb-body-inner">
            <div class="rfb-problem">Multiple agents need to coordinate in real-time — voice agents negotiating, live auctions, streaming services. Solana's 400ms blocks make this possible. Build the interfaces.</div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">What builders create</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Voice agents that negotiate deals with other voice agents</li>
              <li>Live agent auctions where agents bid against each other in real-time</li>
              <li>Streaming payment systems — pay-per-second for agent services</li>
              <li>Real-time collaboration tools where agents work together and split payment dynamically</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Real-time use cases</div>
            <ul class="ql">
              <li>Shopping agent calls a merchant agent, negotiates bulk discount in real-time</li>
              <li>Live compute marketplace: AI needs GPU now, agents bid using instant finality</li>
              <li>Streaming analysis: agent provides live market commentary, paid per second</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="rfb-ex"><div class="rfb-ex-lbl">Example</div><p>"AgentCall" — Shopping agent calls merchant agent, negotiates bulk discount in real-time using Solana's instant finality.</p></div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Traction metrics</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Number of agents and agent startups using your product for coordination</li>
              <li>Number of real-time agent interactions</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rfb-item" id="rfb-3">
        <button class="rfb-trigger" onclick="toggleRFB('rfb-3')">
          <div class="rfb-n">RFB 03</div>
          <div class="rfb-trigger-main">
            <div class="rfb-t-title">Agent Attention Markets</div>
            <div class="rfb-t-sub">You're selling to agents. Traditional marketing doesn't work on AI. What does?</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rfb-toggle">+</div>
        </button>
        <div class="rfb-body">
          <div class="rfb-body-inner">
            <div class="rfb-problem">You are a startup selling to agents. How do you get their attention? Traditional marketing does not work on AI. This is a completely unsolved problem.</div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">What builders create</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Agent advertising platforms where agents pay to promote to other agents</li>
              <li>Priority queues where paying more means faster responses from busy agents</li>
              <li>Agent influencer networks where popular agents endorse services</li>
              <li>Attention bidding systems where agents auction their attention</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Questions worth exploring</div>
            <ul class="ql">
              <li>Do agents develop brands like humans?</li>
              <li>Will there be agent influencers that other agents follow?</li>
              <li>Can you A/B test messaging on agents? What is the ROI?</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="rfb-ex"><div class="rfb-ex-lbl">Example</div><p>"AgentAds" — Google Ads but for AI agents. Providers bid for placement when agents search for services. Solana's low fees enable $0.001 attention bids.</p></div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Traction metrics</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Advertisers onboarded · Agent conversion rate · Cost per agent acquisition</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rfb-item" id="rfb-4">
        <button class="rfb-trigger" onclick="toggleRFB('rfb-4')">
          <div class="rfb-n">RFB 04</div>
          <div class="rfb-trigger-main">
            <div class="rfb-t-title">Emergent Agent Economies</div>
            <div class="rfb-t-sub">What actually happens when hundreds of agents with different goals interact?</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rfb-toggle">+</div>
        </button>
        <div class="rfb-body">
          <div class="rfb-body-inner">
            <div class="rfb-problem">What happens when hundreds of agents with different goals interact on the same network? Can we observe emergent behaviors, and build tools to study them?</div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">What builders create</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Agent simulation environments with real money on Solana</li>
              <li>Tools to observe and analyze agent network dynamics</li>
              <li>Intervention mechanisms: inject agents, change incentives, observe outcomes</li>
              <li>Agent economy analytics: who is trading with who and what patterns emerge</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Research questions</div>
            <ul class="ql">
              <li>Do agent economies develop specialization and division of labor?</li>
              <li>Do agents form cartels or monopolies?</li>
              <li>What economic structures emerge naturally? How do they differ from human economies?</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="rfb-ex"><div class="rfb-ex-lbl">Example</div><p>"AgentWorld" — 100 AI agents with different goals on Solana. Researchers observe what economic structures emerge using real SOL/USDC with safety limits.</p></div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Traction metrics</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Frontier labs interested in using your environment · LOIs from labs for evals</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rfb-item" id="rfb-5">
        <button class="rfb-trigger" onclick="toggleRFB('rfb-5')">
          <div class="rfb-n">RFB 05</div>
          <div class="rfb-trigger-main">
            <div class="rfb-t-title">Multi-Agent Orchestration</div>
            <div class="rfb-t-sub">Complex tasks need multiple agents working together. Who coordinates, and who gets paid?</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rfb-toggle">+</div>
        </button>
        <div class="rfb-body">
          <div class="rfb-body-inner">
            <div class="rfb-problem">Complex tasks require multiple agents working together in real-time. How do they coordinate, communicate, and split payment fairly?</div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">What builders create</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>Multi-agent coordination protocols inspired by workflow orchestration</li>
              <li>Real-time task decomposition where agents bid and self-assemble into teams</li>
              <li>Dynamic payment splitting based on contribution, effort, and quality</li>
              <li>Agent swarm controllers where one agent orchestrates many specialized agents</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Use cases</div>
            <ul class="ql">
              <li>Research: coordinator agent recruits researcher, writer, and editor agents</li>
              <li>Content production: idea, writer, editor, and designer agents in sequence</li>
              <li>Live event coverage: multiple agents streaming different angles, paid by contribution</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="rfb-ex"><div class="rfb-ex-lbl">Example</div><p>"SwarmOS" — Submit a complex task, agents self-assemble using a Solana marketplace, complete the work, and auto-split payment based on contribution tracked on-chain.</p></div>
            <div class="sub-lbl">Traction metrics</div>
            <ul class="bl">
              <li>LOIs from labs for orchestration evals · Agent runtimes using your workflow</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- EARLY BUILDER EXAMPLES -->
<div class="section" id="examples">
  <div class="sec-label">
    <div class="sec-label-text">Early<br>Builder<br>Examples</div>
    <div class="sec-label-num">04</div>
  </div>
  <div class="sec-body">
    <p class="rfb-intro" style="margin-bottom:20px;">Research that points directly to buildable products. Starting points, not prescriptions.</p>
    <div class="example-list">
      <div class="example-item">
        <div class="example-header">
          <div class="example-n">01</div>
          <div>
            <div class="example-title">Debate Primitives for Multi-Agent LLM Collaboration</div>
            <div class="example-attr">Li et al., 2025 · UW-Madison</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="example-body">
          <div class="example-desc">Structured debate between LLMs improves factual accuracy and reduces hallucination. A foundation for building coordination protocols where agents argue, verify, and reach consensus before settling on-chain.</div>
          <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.06243" target="_blank" class="example-link">arxiv.org ↗</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="example-item">
        <div class="example-header">
          <div class="example-n">02</div>
          <div>
            <div class="example-title">Scaling LLM-as-Judge with ELO Reputation Systems</div>
            <div class="example-attr">Chiang et al., 2024 · UC Berkeley</div>
          </div>
